President Obama announced his intent to nominate four individuals to key administration posts. Constance Smith Barker is nominated for Member of the Equal Employment Opportunity Commission. She currently serves as Commissioner of the EEOC and has a background in law and education. Daniel M. Gallagher is nominated for Commissioner of the Securities and Exchange Commission. He has experience in regulatory issues and market-related enforcement matters. Charles R. Korsmo is nominated for Member of the Board of Trustees of the Barry Goldwater Scholarship and Excellence in Education Foundation. He is currently an Assistant Professor of Law at Case Western Reserve University and has experience in environmental policy and legislation. John H. Yopp is nominated for Member of the Board of Trustees of the Barry Goldwater Scholarship and Excellence in Education Foundation. He currently holds various positions at the University of Kentucky and has a background in academia and educational initiatives.